{"type":"message","id":"93de4936","parentId":"7e765561","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:55:02.505Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the music API at /api/music is going to `http://localhost:3001` but there's nothing running on 3001. And `/tools` goes to the gateway. Let me check if there's an API server running on a different port, or if the vite dev server is what should be running. Let me also check the `server.cjs` more carefully.\n\nWait - the server.cjs is what's running on port 8787 (process 19835), but it only handles `/tools` proxying and static files from `/dist`. It doesn't have any `/api/music` or `/api/emails` route. So those would be going to... the Vite dev server? But port 3001 doesn't seem to be running.\n\n\nBut `/api/music` actually returned valid JSON from the production build, so the server is running and serving responses — it just might be getting proxied elsewhere or there's something else handling that route that I'm missing.\n","thinkingSignature":"0791a410edfa0b2f2bb83dae8f966d565330c62e79550504006a12562d220f0c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_suyv0duf3juq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://100.103.22.35:8787/api/emails 2>&1 | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_suyv0duf3juq_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/agent-mission-control/dist/ && echo \"---\" && ls ~/agent-mission-control/dist/assets/ 2>/dev/null | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":400,"output":298,"cacheRead":51712,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52410,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777787695263,"responseId":"0646162fc6abe58adefcf056b212d360"}}
