{"type":"message","id":"f3b7150c","parentId":"3a31047c","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:55:34.400Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_azl2zwmrv9ub_3","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"finnly\":[{\"date\":\"May 3, 2026\",\"waterAM\":false,\"waterPM\":false,\"breakfast\":false,\"dinner\":false,\"walk1\":false,\"walk2\":false,\"walk3\":false,\"walk1Poop\":false,\"walk2Poop\":false,\"walk3Poop\":false,\"treats\":0}]}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1198,"aggregated":"{\"finnly\":[{\"date\":\"May 3, 2026\",\"waterAM\":false,\"waterPM\":false,\"breakfast\":false,\"dinner\":false,\"walk1\":false,\"walk2\":false,\"walk3\":false,\"walk1Poop\":false,\"walk2Poop\":false,\"walk3Poop\":false,\"treats\":0}]}","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777787734400}}
{"type":"message","id":"49d53b60","parentId":"f3b7150c","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:55:39.888Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All data is persisting correctly. Let me now check the MoneyWidget and HabitsWidget to see how they handle input and data saving. And also check the FinnnlyWidget.\n\nLet me also look at the MoneyWidget to see if it has an \"add\" input feature, since Bobby wants to make sure \"when I input anything, it saves and keeps track of stuff.\"\n","thinkingSignature":"7529b663f8715467c76bfb489761542e93df7fee5bc1f419624261e4716bdb83"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nAll data is persisting. Now let me check the widgets that have input fields to make sure the add/save flow works:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a7rccj40pd2s_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/components/MoneyWidget.tsx"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a7rccj40pd2s_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/src/components/HabitsWidget.tsx"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":476,"output":181,"cacheRead":69120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69777,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777787734401,"responseId":"06461656198c3d46d36f977844abd747"}}
{"type":"message","id":"242e7487","parentId":"49d53b60","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:55:39.918Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a7rccj40pd2s_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { useState, useEffect, useRef } from 'react';\n\ntype Account = 'bobby' | 'logan' | 'dash';\ntype MoneyType = 'income' | 'expense';\n\ninterface MoneyEntry {\n  id: string;\n  date: string;\n  description: string;\n  amount: number;\n  type: MoneyType;\n}\n\ninterface Balances {\n  bobby: number;\n  logan: number;\n  dash: number;\n}\n\nconst fmt = (n: number) => n.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 });\n\nconst ACC_COLORS: Record<Account, { bg: string; border: string; text: string; label: string }> = {\n  bobby:  { bg: 'bg-emerald-500/20', border: 'border-emerald-500/30', text: 'text-emerald-400', label: 'Bobby' },\n  logan:  { bg: 'bg-blue-500/20',   border: 'border-blue-500/30',   text: 'text-blue-400',   label: 'Logan' },\n  dash:   { bg: 'bg-orange-500/20', border: 'border-orange-500/30', text: 'text-orange-400',  label: 'Dash' },\n};\n\nexport function MoneyWidget() {\n  const [account, setAccount] = useState<Account>('bobby');\n  const [entries, setEntries] = useState<MoneyEntry[]>([]);\n  const [balances, setBalances] = useState<Balances>({ bobby: 0, logan: 0, dash: 0 });\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const hasLoaded = useRef(true);\n\n  const [amount, setAmount] = useState('');\n  const [description, setDescription] = useState('');\n  const [isIncome, setIsIncome] = useState(false);\n  const [showHistory, setShowHistory] = useState(false);\n  const [showTotals, setShowTotals] = useState(false);\n  const [editingBalance, setEditingBalance] = useState(false);\n  const [editValue, setEditValue] = useState('');\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    Promise.all([\n      fetch('/api/money').then(r => r.json()),\n      fetch('/api/money/balances').then(r => r.json()).catch(() => ({ bobby: 0, logan: 0, dash: 0 }))\n    ]).then(([moneyData, balancesData]) => {\n      setEntries(moneyData.money || []);\n      setBalances(balancesData);\n      if (hasLoaded.current) {\n        setLoading(false);\n        hasLoaded.current = false;\n      }\n    }).catch(() => {\n      if (hasLoaded.current) {\n        setLoading(false);\n        hasLoaded.current = false;\n      }\n    });\n  }, []);\n\n\n  // Use saved balance for selected account\n  const balance = balances[account];\n  const colors = ACC_COLORS[account];\n\n  const saveBalance = async (newBalances: Balances) => {\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch('/api/money/balances', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n        body: JSON.stringify(newBalances),\n      });\n      if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Failed to save');\n      setBalances(newBalances);\n    } catch (e) {\n      console.error('Failed to save balance', e);\n    }\n  };\n\n  const startEditBalance = () => {\n    setEditValue(balance.toFixed(2));\n    setEditingBalance(true);\n  };\n\n  const saveEditBalance = () => {\n    const newValue = parseFloat(editValue);\n    if (isNaN(newValue)) return;\n    const newBalances = { ...balances, [account]: newValue };\n    saveBalance(newBalances);\n    setEditingBalance(false);\n  };\n\n  const handleAdd = async () => {\n    const numAmount = parseFloat(amount);\n    if (isNaN(numAmount) || numAmount <= 0 || !description.trim()) return;\n\n    const item: MoneyEntry = {\n      id: Date.now().toString(),\n      date: new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'short', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' }),\n      description: description.trim(),\n      amount: isIncome ? numAmount : -numAmount,\n      type: isIncome ? 'income' : 'expense',\n    };\n\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch('/api/money/action', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n        body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'add', item }),\n      });\n      const data = await res.json();\n      if (!res.ok) throw new Error(data.error || 'Add failed');\n      setEntries(data.money || [item, ...entries]);\n\n      // Auto-update and save the account balance\n      const newBalances = { ...balances, [account]: balances[account] + item.amount };\n      const saveRes = await fetch('/api/money/balances', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n        body: JSON.stringify(newBalances),\n      });\n      if (saveRes.ok) setBalances(newBalances);\n    } catch (e: unknown) {\n      alert(e instanceof Error ? e.message : 'Failed to add entry');\n    }\n\n    setAmount('');\n    setDescription('');\n  };\n\n  const handleDelete = async (id: string) => {\n    const entry = entries.find(e => e.id === id);\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch('/api/money/action', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n        body: JSON.stringify({ action: 'delete', item: { id } }),\n      });\n      const data = await res.json();\n      if (!res.ok) throw new Error(data.error || 'Delete failed');\n      setEntries(data.money || entries.filter(e => e.id !== id));\n\n      // Auto-update and save the account balance (reverse the deleted amount)\n      if (entry) {\n        const newBalances = { ...balances, [account]: balances[account] - entry.amount };\n        const saveRes = await fetch('/api/money/balances', {\n          method: 'POST',\n          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n          body: JSON.stringify(newBalances),\n        });\n        if (saveRes.ok) setBalances(newBalances);\n      }\n    } catch (e: unknown) {\n      alert(e instanceof Error ? e.message : 'Failed to delete entry');\n    }\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <>\n      <div className=\"backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/[0.10] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden\">\n        {/* Header */}\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-4 border-b border-white/[0.06]\">\n          <span className=\"text-xl\">💰</span>\n          <p className=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wider\">Money Tracker</p>\n          <div className=\"ml-auto flex items-center gap-2\">\n            <button\n              onClick={() => setShowTotals(true)}\n              className=\"px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-xs font-medium bg-white/[0.05] hover:bg-white/[0.10] text-slate-300 border border-white/[0.10] transition-colors\"\n            >\n              Totals\n            </button>\n            {!loading && entries.length > 0 && (\n              <button\n                onClick={() => setShowHistory(true)}\n                className=\"px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-xs font-medium bg-white/[0.05] hover:bg-white/[0.10] text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/20 transition-colors\"\n              >\n                History ({entries.length})\n              </button>\n            )}\n            <div className=\"w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-400\" />\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Account Toggle */}\n        <div className=\"px-5 py-3 border-b border-white/[0.06]\">\n          <div className=\"flex gap-2\">\n            {(['bobby', 'logan', 'dash'] as Account[]).map(a => (\n              <button\n                key={a}\n                onClick={() => setAccount(a)}\n                className={`flex-1 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-colors ${\n                  account === a\n                    ? `${ACC_COLORS[a].bg} ${ACC_COLORS[a].text} ${ACC_COLORS[a].border} border`\n                    : 'text-slate-500 border border-transparent'\n                }`}\n              >\n                {ACC_COLORS[a].label}\n              </button>\n            ))}\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Balance */}\n        <div className=\"px-5 py-5 text-center border-b border-white/[0.06]\">\n          <p className={`text-[10px] uppercase tracking-wider mb-1 ${colors.text} opacity-70`}>\n            {colors.label} {account === 'dash' ? 'Dasher Card' : 'Checking'}\n          </p>\n          {loading ? (\n            <div className=\"h-10 w-40 mx-auto bg-white/[0.04] rounded-lg animate-pulse\" />\n          ) : editingBalance ? (\n            <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center gap-2\">\n              <span className=\"text-3xl font-mono font-semibold text-slate-400\">$</span>\n              <input\n                type=\"number\"\n                step=\"0.01\"\n                value={editValue}\n                onChange={e => setEditValue(e.target.value)}\n                onKeyDown={e => { if (e.key === 'Enter') saveEditBalance(); if (e.key === 'Escape') setEditingBalance(false); }}\n                className=\"w-32 bg-black/20 border border-white/20 rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-3xl font-mono font-semibold text-slate-100 text-center focus:outline-none focus:border-emerald-500/50\"\n                autoFocus\n              />\n              <button onClick={saveEditBalance} className=\"px-3 py-2 rounded-lg bg-emerald-500/30 text-emerald-400 text-sm font-medium\">Save</button>\n              <button onClick={() => setEditingBalance(false)} className=\"px-3 py-2 rounded-lg bg-white/10 text-slate-400 text-sm\">Cancel</button>\n            </div>\n          ) : (\n            <button onClick={startEditBalance} className=\"group\">\n              <span className={`text-3xl font-mono font-semibold ${balance >= 0 ? 'text-slate-100' : 'text-red-400'}`}>\n                ${fmt(Math.abs(balance))}\n              </span>\n              <span className=\"text-lg ml-1 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-50 transition-opacity\">✏️</span>\n            </button>\n          )}\n          <p className=\"text-[9px] text-slate-600 mt-1\">tap balance to edit</p>\n        </div>\n\n        {/* Entry Form */}\n        <div className=\"px-5 py-4\">\n          <form onSubmit={e => { e.preventDefault(); handleAdd(); }} className=\"space-y-2.5\">\n            <div className=\"flex gap-2\">\n              <button\n                type=\"button\"\n                onClick={() => setIsIncome(false)}\n                className={`flex-1 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-colors ${\n                  !isIncome\n                    ? 'bg-red-500/20 text-red-400 border border-red-500/30'\n                    : 'text-slate-500 border border-transparent'\n                }`}\n              >\n                Expense\n              </button>\n              <button\n                type=\"button\"\n                onClick={() => setIsIncome(true)}\n                className={`flex-1 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-colors ${\n                  isIncome\n                    ? 'bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/30'\n                    : 'text-slate-500 border border-transparent'\n                }`}\n              >\n                Income\n              </button>\n            </div>\n\n            <div className=\"flex gap-2\">\n              <input\n                type=\"number\"\n                step=\"0.01\"\n                min=\"0.01\"\n                value={amount}\n                onChange={e => setAmount(e.target.value)}\n                placeholder=\"$0.00\"\n                className=\"w-28 bg-white/[0.06] border border-white/[0.10] rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm text-slate-100 placeholder-slate-600 focus:outline-none focus:border-emerald-500/50 font-mono text-right flex-shrink-0\"\n              />\n              <input\n                type=\"text\"\n                value={description}\n                onChange={e => setDescription(e.target.value)}\n                placeholder=\"Label (e.g. Groceries, Paycheck)\"\n                className=\"flex-1 bg-white/[0.06] border border-white/[0.10] rounded-lg px-3 py-2 text-sm text-slate-100 placeholder-slate-600 focus:outline-none focus:border-emerald-500/50\"\n              />\n            </div>\n\n            <button\n              type=\"submit\"\n              className={`w-full py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium transition-colors ${\n                isIncome\n                  ? 'bg-emerald-500/20 hover:bg-emerald-500/30 text-emerald-400 border border-emerald-500/30'\n                  : 'bg-red-500/20 hover:bg-red-500/30 text-red-400 border border-red-500/30'\n              }`}\n            >\n              {isIncome ? '+ Add Income' : '- Add Expense'}\n            </button>\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\n                <p className=\"text-2xl font-mono font-semibold text-slate-100\">${fmt(balance)}</p>\n                <p className=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">net balance</p>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"px-5 pb-6 max-h-80 overflow-y-auto\">\n              <div className=\"space-y-1\">\n                {entries.map(entry => (\n                  <div key={entry.id} className=\"group flex items-start justify-between gap-3 py-2.5 border-b border-white/[0.05]\">\n                    <div className=\"flex items-start gap-3 min-w-0\">\n                      <div className={`w-2 h-2 rounded-full mt-2 flex-shrink-0 ${entry.amount >= 0 ? 'bg-emerald-400' : 'bg-red-400'}`} />\n                      <div className=\"min-w-0\">\n                        <p className=\"text-sm text-slate-200 font-medium\">{entry.description}</p>\n                        <p className=\"text-xs text-slate-500\">{entry.date}</p>\n                      </div>\n                    </div>\n                    <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2 flex-shrink-0\">\n                      <span className={`text-base font-mono font-semibold ${entry.amount >= 0 ? 'text-emerald-400' : 'text-red-400'}`}>\n                        {entry.amount > 0 ? '+' : ''}${fmt(Math.abs(entry.amount))}\n                      </span>\n                      <button\n                        onClick={() => handleDelete(entry.id)}\n                        className=\"w-5 h-5 flex items-center justify-center rounded text-slate-600 hover:text-red-400 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity text-xs flex-shrink-0\"\n                      >\n                        ✕\n                      </button>\n                    </div>\n                  </div>\n                ))}\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      {/* Totals Modal */}\n      {showTotals && (\n        <div className=\"fixed inset-0 z-50 flex items-end justify-center\">\n          <div className=\"absolute inset-0 bg-black/50 backdrop-blur-sm\" onClick={() => setShowTotals(false)} />\n          <div className=\"relative w-full max-w-md mx-auto rounded-t-2xl bg-slate-900/95 backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/[0.15] overflow-hidden animate-slideUp\">\n            <div className=\"flex justify-center pt-3 pb-2\">\n              <div className=\"w-10 h-1 rounded-full bg-white/20\" />\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"flex items-center gap-4 px-5 pb-4\">\n              <span className=\"text-4xl\">💵</span>\n              <div>\n                <h3 className=\"text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100\">Total Balance</h3>\n                <p className=\"text-sm text-slate-400\">All Accounts Combined</p>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n            <div className=\"px-5 pb-6 space-y-3\">\n              <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between py-2\">\n                <p className=\"text-sm text-emerald-400 font-medium\">Bobby Checking</p>\n                <p className=\"text-base font-mono text-emerald-400\">${fmt(balances.bobby)}</p>\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between py-2\">\n                <p className=\"text-sm text-blue-400 font-medium\">Logan Checking</p>\n                <p className=\"text-base font-mono text-blue-400\">${fmt(balances.logan)}</p>\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between py-2\">\n                <p className=\"text-sm text-orange-400 font-medium\">Dash Dasher</p>\n                <p className=\"text-base font-mono text-orange-400\">${fmt(balances.dash)}</p>\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"flex items-center justify-between py-3 border-t border-white/[0.15] mt-2\">\n                <p className=\"text-base font-semibold text-slate-200\">Total</p>\n                <p className=\"text-xl font-mono font-bold text-slate-100\">${fmt(balances.bobby + balances.logan + balances.dash)}</p>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n    </>\n  );\n}\n[... 917 more characters truncated]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777787739917}}
{"type":"message","id":"e84fa940","parentId":"242e7487","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:55:39.919Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a7rccj40pd2s_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';\n\ninterface DailyHabit {\n  date: string;\n  water: number;\n  stretch: number;\n  laundry: boolean;\n  bedMade: boolean;\n  vacuum: number;\n  breakfast: boolean;\n  lunch: boolean;\n  dinner: boolean;\n}\n\ninterface TaskDef {\n  key: string;\n  label: string;\n  emoji: string;\n  type: 'bool' | 'count';\n}\n\nconst TASKS: TaskDef[] = [\n  { key: 'bedMade', label: 'Bed Made', emoji: '🛏️', type: 'bool' },\n  { key: 'breakfast', label: 'Breakfast', emoji: '🍳', type: 'bool' },\n  { key: 'lunch', label: 'Lunch', emoji: '🥪', type: 'bool' },\n  { key: 'dinner', label: 'Dinner', emoji: '🍽️', type: 'bool' },\n  { key: 'laundry', label: 'Laundry', emoji: '👕', type: 'bool' },\n  { key: 'vacuum', label: 'Vacuum', emoji: '🧹', type: 'count' },\n  { key: 'water', label: 'Water', emoji: '💧', type: 'count' },\n  { key: 'stretch', label: 'Stretch', emoji: '🧘', type: 'count' },\n];\n\nexport function HabitsWidget() {\n  const [days, setDays] = useState<DailyHabit[]>([]);\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n  const [tracker, setTracker] = useState<{ dayIdx: number; task: TaskDef } | null>(null);\n\n  const fetchData = async () => {\n    try {\n      const res = await fetch('/api/habits');\n      const data = await res.json();\n      setDays(data.habits || []);\n    } catch (e) { console.error('Failed to fetch', e); }\n    finally { setLoading(false); }\n  };\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetchData();\n    const id = setInterval(fetchData, 2000);\n    return () => clearInterval(id);\n  }, []);\n\n  const saveData = async (newDays: DailyHabit[]) => {\n    try {\n      await fetch('/api/habits', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n        body: JSON.stringify({ habits: newDays }),\n      });\n      setDays(newDays);\n    } catch (e) { console.error('Failed to save', e); }\n  };\n\n  const toggleTask = (dayIndex: number, key: string) => {\n    const newDays = [...days];\n    const day = { ...newDays[dayIndex] };\n    (day as Record<string, unknown>)[key] = !(day as Record<string, unknown>)[key];\n    newDays[dayIndex] = day;\n    saveData(newDays);\n  };\n\n  const incrementTask = (dayIndex: number, key: string) => {\n    const newDays = [...days];\n    const day = { ...newDays[dayIndex] };\n    (day as Record<string, unknown>)[key] = ((day as Record<string, unknown>)[key] as number) + 1;\n    newDays[dayIndex] = day;\n    saveData(newDays);\n  };\n\n  const decrementTask = (dayIndex: number, key: string) => {\n    const newDays = [...days];\n    const day = { ...newDays[dayIndex] };\n    const current = (day as Record<string, unknown>)[key] as number;\n    if (current > 0) {\n      (day as Record<string, unknown>)[key] = current - 1;\n      newDays[dayIndex] = day;\n      saveData(newDays);\n    }\n  };\n\n  const isToday = (dateStr: string) => {\n    if (typeof dateStr !== 'string') return true; // default to today if malformed\n    const parts = dateStr.match(/^(\\w+)\\s+(\\d+),\\s+(\\d+)$/);\n    if (!parts) return true;\n    const months = ['Jan','Feb','Mar','Apr','May','Jun','Jul','Aug','Sep','Oct','Nov','Dec'];\n    const mon = months.indexOf(parts[1]);\n    const day = parseInt(parts[2]);\n    const yr = parseInt(parts[3]);\n    const d = new Date();\n    return d.getFullYear() === yr && d.getMonth() === mon && d.getDate() === day;\n  };\n\n  const getValue = (day: DailyHabit, key: string) => (day as unknown as Record<string, unknown>)[key];\n\n  const currentValue = tracker ? getValue(days[tracker.dayIdx], tracker.task.key) as number : 0;\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"backdrop-blur-xl border border-white/[0.10] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden\">\n      <div className=\"px-4 py-3 border-b border-white/[0.06]\">\n        <div className=\"flex items-center gap-2\">\n          <span className=\"text-xl\">📋</span>\n          <p className=\"text-[11px] font-semibold text-slate-400 uppercase tracking-wider\">Daily Habits</p>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n\n      {loading ? (\n        <div className=\"p-4 space-y-2\">\n          {[100, 80].map((w,i) => <div key={i} className=\"h-16 bg-white/[0.05] rounded animate-pulse\" style={{width:w+'%'}} />)}\n        </div>\n      ) : days.length === 0 ? (\n        <div className=\"p-4 text-center\">\n          <p className=\"text-[10px] text-slate-500\">No data yet</p>\n        </div>\n      ) : (\n        <div className=\"p-4 space-y-6\">\n          {days.filter((d: DailyHabit) => isToday(d.date)).map((day, dayIdx) => (\n            <div key={day.date} className=\"space-y-3\">\n              <p className=\"text-sm font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase\">{day.date}</p>\n              <div className=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-4\">\n                {TASKS.map(({ key, label, emoji, type }) => {\n                  const value = getValue(day, key);\n                  if (type === 'bool') {\n                    const boolVal = value as boolean;\n                    return (\n                      <button\n                        key={key}\n                        onClick={() => toggleTask(dayIdx, key)}\n                        className=\"flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 rounded text-sm font-medium transition-all border border-white/[0.06] hover:bg-white/[0.05]\"\n                      >\n                        <span className=\"w-8 text-center text-base leading-none\">{emoji}</span>\n                        <span className={boolVal ? 'text-emerald-400' : 'text-slate-500'}>{label}</span>\n                        {boolVal && <span className=\"ml-auto text-emerald-400\">✓</span>}\n                      </button>\n                    );\n                  } else {\n                    const countVal = value as number;\n                    return (\n                      <button\n                        key={key}\n                        onClick={() => setTracker({ dayIdx, task: { key, label, emoji, type } })}\n                        className=\"flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 rounded text-sm font-medium transition-all border border-white/[0.06] hover:bg-white/[0.05]\"\n                      >\n                        <span className=\"w-8 text-center text-base leading-none\">{emoji}</span>\n                        <span className=\"text-slate-400\">{label}</span>\n                        <span className=\"ml-auto text-slate-300 font-mono text-base\">{countVal}</span>\n                      </button>\n                    );\n                  }\n                })}\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          ))}\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      {/* Tracker popup */}\n      {tracker && (\n        <div className=\"fixed inset-0 z-50 flex items-center justify-center p-4\">\n          <div className=\"absolute inset-0 bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-sm\" onClick={() => setTracker(null)} />\n          <div className=\"relative w-full max-w-sm rounded-2xl border border-white/[0.15] bg-slate-900/95 backdrop-blur-xl p-8 flex flex-col items-center gap-6\">\n            <p className=\"text-4xl\">{tracker.task.emoji}</p>\n            <p className=\"text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-100\">{tracker.task.label}</p>\n            <div className=\"flex items-center gap-8\">\n              <button\n                onClick={() => decrementTask(tracker.dayIdx, tracker.task.key)}\n                className=\"w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 text-slate-100 text-4xl font-bold flex items-center justify-center transition-colors\"\n              >\n                −\n              </button>\n              <span className=\"text-6xl font-mono font-bold text-slate-100 w-20 text-center\">{currentValue}</span>\n              <button\n                onClick={() => incrementTask(tracker.dayIdx, tracker.task.key)}\n                className=\"w-20 h-20 rounded-2xl bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 text-slate-100 text-4xl font-bold flex items-center justify-center transition-colors\"\n              >\n                +\n              </button>\n            </div>\n            <button onClick={() => setTracker(null)} className=\"text-slate-500 text-sm hover:text-slate-300 transition-colors\">Done</button>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777787739918}}
{"type":"message","id":"53141c6c","parentId":"e84fa940","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:55:49.217Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so the app is working. Let me now test the critical input flows. Let me send Bobby a quick summary of what I found and what needs to be fixed, then ask what specifically he wants me to fix.\n\nActually, he asked me to \"make sure everything is good.\" Let me think about what that means:\n\n1. **MoneyWidget** - Input saves and tracks entries. ✅ Working - POST /api/money/action adds entries, POST /api/money/balances saves balances. The money data file is being read/written correctly.\n\n2. **MusicWidget** - Uses Apple Music (osascript commands via /api/music). This should be working since the API responds. But let me check if the Music app is actually running.\n   \n3. **EmailWidget** - Fetches emails via /api/emails which calls `gog gmail search newer_than:1d -j`. This should be working since the API returned email data.\n\nNow I'm going through the actual widget code to verify the state management and persistence are set up correctly. The HabitsWidget is already set up properly, so let me check the other components like MusicWidget to see if they're handling state and data persistence the same way.\n","thinkingSignature":"e56d929e171bcc7fcb64cd0a0dc50ebbb42501f560cd7ea220526087ba5cb17f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sejdmnfoyucg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:3001/api/music 2>&1 && echo \"---\" && osascript -e 'tell application \"Music\" to player state as string' 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6617,"output":314,"cacheRead":69504,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76435,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777787739923,"responseId":"0646165cb156308d1c649f0a01287f97"}}
