{"type":"message","id":"7faec518","parentId":"8213012a","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:56:06.731Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the money API is working. Now let me clean up the test entry and summarize the status for Bobby.\n","thinkingSignature":"87d695d5522b9eddeb0fafdbd9fa8d548054342af4b086748c991827697170b5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cktfpsx2f4og_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Clean up the test entry\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/money/action \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"action\":\"delete\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"test123\"}}' 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":426,"output":102,"cacheRead":76096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76624,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777787756677,"responseId":"0646166c384a9703a26b96c51e34148a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"530d899a","parentId":"7faec518","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:56:06.814Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_cktfpsx2f4og_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"ok\":true,\"money\":[{\"id\":\"1776997143330\",\"date\":\"Apr 23, 2026\",\"description\":\"Capitol One Payment\",\"amount\":-50,\"type\":\"expense\"},{\"id\":\"1774806831424\",\"date\":\"Mar 29, 2026\",\"description\":\"Chase Payment\",\"amount\":-74,\"type\":\"expense\"},{\"id\":\"1774806822474\",\"date\":\"Mar 29, 2026\",\"description\":\"Apple Card Payment\",\"amount\":-60,\"type\":\"expense\"},{\"id\":\"1774806812959\",\"date\":\"Mar 29, 2026\",\"description\":\"Capitol One - QuickSilver\",\"amount\":-411,\"type\":\"expense\"}]}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":54,"aggregated":"{\"ok\":true,\"money\":[{\"id\":\"1776997143330\",\"date\":\"Apr 23, 2026\",\"description\":\"Capitol One Payment\",\"amount\":-50,\"type\":\"expense\"},{\"id\":\"1774806831424\",\"date\":\"Mar 29, 2026\",\"description\":\"Chase Payment\",\"amount\":-74,\"type\":\"expense\"},{\"id\":\"1774806822474\",\"date\":\"Mar 29, 2026\",\"description\":\"Apple Card Payment\",\"amount\":-60,\"type\":\"expense\"},{\"id\":\"1774806812959\",\"date\":\"Mar 29, 2026\",\"description\":\"Capitol One - QuickSilver\",\"amount\":-411,\"type\":\"expense\"}]}","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-cody"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777787766814}}
{"type":"message","id":"a43945b8","parentId":"530d899a","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:56:17.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the money API works correctly. Now let me also check the habits API and the finnly API, and also test a POST to finnly.\n\nActually, I think the main issue Bobby might be experiencing is that the Mission Control web app at http://100.103.22.35:8787/ is the built dist version. The server that's running on port 8787 is the static file server, but it proxies /tools to the gateway at 18789. But the API calls to /api/music and /api/emails go to port 3001 (from vite.config.ts proxy settings).\n\nWait, actually in the dist built version, the proxy settings from vite.config.ts don't apply. \n\nSo the built static files need to know the actual API server URL. Looking at how the MusicWidget.tsx makes API calls, it's hitting '/api/music' and '/api/emails', but those would only resolve to localhost:3001 if the static server is proxying those paths. Let me check the server.cjs to see if it's actually doing that proxying or if the built app needs to be configured with the actual API endpoint.\n","thinkingSignature":"a6141d46fe9bce34c839719b46fe2e29368d355d3fe80928d9c482937ac35e51"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2hbmi1odiplm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/server.cjs"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":346,"output":275,"cacheRead":76416,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77037,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777787766818,"responseId":"06461676e99e3923b14f4e1f433ac945"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1a059c1","parentId":"a43945b8","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:56:17.528Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2hbmi1odiplm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\n\nconst PORT = 8787;\nconst GATEWAY_TOKEN = '286cab…1111';\nconst DIST_DIR = path.join(__dirname, 'dist');\n\nconst mimeTypes = {\n  '.html': 'text/html; charset=utf-8',\n  '.js': 'application/javascript',\n  '.css': 'text/css',\n  '.json': 'application/json',\n  '.png': 'image/png',\n  '.jpg': 'image/jpeg',\n  '.svg': 'image/svg+xml',\n  '.ico': 'image/x-icon',\n  '.woff': 'font/woff',\n  '.woff2': 'font/woff2',\n};\n\nconst server = http.createServer((req, res) => {\n  // CORS\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, Authorization');\n  res.setHeader('Access-Control-Allow-Credentials', 'true');\n\n  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {\n    res.writeHead(204);\n    res.end();\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Proxy /tools to gateway\n  if (req.url.startsWith('/tools')) {\n    let body = '';\n    req.on('data', chunk => { body += chunk; });\n    req.on('end', () => {\n      const options = {\n        hostname: '127.0.0.1',\n        port: 18789,\n        path: req.url,\n        method: 'POST',\n        headers: {\n          'Content-Type': 'application/json',\n          'Authorization': `Bearer ${GATEWAY_TOKEN}`,\n          'Content-Length': Buffer.byteLength(body),\n        },\n      };\n      const proxyReq = http.request(options, (proxyRes) => {\n        const headers = {\n          ...proxyRes.headers,\n          'Access-Control-Allow-Origin': '*',\n          'Access-Control-Allow-Methods': 'GET, POST, OPTIONS',\n          'Access-Control-Allow-Headers': 'Content-Type, Authorization',\n        };\n        res.writeHead(proxyRes.statusCode, headers);\n        proxyRes.pipe(res, { end: true });\n      });\n      proxyReq.on('error', (e) => {\n        console.error('Proxy error:', e.message);\n        res.writeHead(502);\n        res.end(JSON.stringify({ error: e.message }));\n      });\n      if (body) proxyReq.write(body);\n      proxyReq.end();\n    });\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve static files from dist/\n  let urlPath = req.url.split('?')[0];\n  \n  // Handle SPA hash routes - serve index.html\n  if (urlPath === '/' || urlPath === '' || urlPath.startsWith('/#') || urlPath === '/index.html') {\n    urlPath = '/index.html';\n  }\n  \n  const filePath = path.join(DIST_DIR, urlPath);\n  const ext = path.extname(filePath);\n  const contentType = mimeTypes[ext] || 'application/octet-stream';\n\n  fs.readFile(filePath, (err, data) => {\n    if (err) {\n      // Try index.html for SPA\n      fs.readFile(path.join(DIST_DIR, 'index.html'), (err2, data2) => {\n        if (err2) {\n          console.error('404:', req.url, err2.message);\n          res.writeHead(404);\n          res.end('Not found: ' + req.url);\n        } else {\n          res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/html; charset=utf-8' });\n          res.end(data2);\n        }\n      });\n    } else {\n      res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': contentType });\n      res.end(data);\n    }\n  });\n});\n\nserver.listen(PORT, '0.0.0.0', () => {\n  console.log(`Agent Chat running on http://0.0.0.0:${PORT}`);\n  console.log(`Gateway proxy: http://127.0.0.1:18789/tools`);\n});\n\nprocess.on('SIGTERM', () => { server.close(); process.exit(0); });\nprocess.on('SIGINT', () => { server.close(); process.exit(0); });\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777787777528}}
{"type":"message","id":"b1568986","parentId":"c1a059c1","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:56:24.543Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue now. The `server.cjs` doesn't proxy `/api` requests to port 3001 where the API is running. The `vite.config.ts` proxies `/api` to `http://localhost:3001`, but `server.cjs` (which serves the built `dist/` files) doesn't have that proxy.\n\nHowever, the dist version IS being served, and the Vite proxy only works in dev mode. So either:\n1. The dist HTML files are hardcoded to call the API directly at port 3001\n2. The dist has some other configuration\n\nLet me check the built dist HTML to see what URLs it's using.\n","thinkingSignature":"c3c666b58305e1fac8f70a1b1e9f359b25dd5af8daa953b1c181055635f2002b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1zx9n4h2uuff_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/agent-mission-control/dist/index.html | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1067,"output":173,"cacheRead":76672,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77912,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777787777531,"responseId":"06461681406b52a0e55414e900529905"}}
