{"type":"message","id":"eeb4eeb2","parentId":"bad615b7","timestamp":"2026-05-03T05:57:07.351Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Habits save works! Now let me verify it persisted and check the HabitsWidget behavior when I check it. Also let me check the finnly saving.\n\nThe issue is that HabitsWidget doesn't save properly when you click tasks. Looking at the code again:\n\n```js\nconst saveData = async (newDays: DailyHabit[]) => {\n  try {\n    await fetch('/api/habits', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ habits: newDays }),\n    });\n    setDays(newDays);\n  } catch (e) { console.error('Failed to save', e); }\n};\n\n\n```\n\nThis sends `habits: newDays` which matches what the server expects. The flow seems correct, but the habits data has a different structure than what the server returns - the widget is sending extra fields like `laundry`, `bedMade`, and `vacuum` that might be causing issues with how the server processes the update.\n\n```\n","thinkingSignature":"2061fb751807600dd5c29cf542257d71ed0c27e395f79769199ddd708394d7b7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r3xza2twy3t7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what habits got saved\ncurl -s http://localhost:3001/api/habits"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":284,"output":252,"cacheRead":85952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86488,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777787821478,"responseId":"064616adb82ac9248d038250704755d0"}}
